metadata.name: Abstract Life #241
metadata.description:
The concept of organic, obtained from living systems, is said to be an effect that, like a plant and a living being, has grown in a completely dynamic manner in different degrees, and no factor except vital forces has prevented its growth. Organic creation is an example of this type. LÃ©onard de Vinci believed in nature; he wrote, "Painting is a child of nature" in his opinion, art should be compatible with nature. His public image of creativity was "innovation while maintaining fidelity" to nature. According to Michelangelo, the form the artist gives to the materials is in the artist's mind and the materials themselves. Therefore, the artist is always in a metaphysical struggle with the form and secrets of nature. This is a revelatory process through which the artist discovers the mass of paper already hidden in his mind and the materials. As an architect, I tried to create this work while paying attention to the structuralism of shapes and forms in creation, inspired by the colors in nature and my experience in painting and illustration.

To spread the vibe of my beautiful community, minters will own 50% of royalty on each secondary sale.
Eighteen different color palettes and three different borders are used in this artwork.
Made in p5js
Created August 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #2400
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

We meet shapes of all kinds in our life.

Algorithmic randomness generates shapes ever so slightly different yet similar. 
I suppose these are someoneâs collection.

âWhy do they need to have so many similar things?â

Perhaps itâs their versatility in the pleasure they could bring.
Perhaps theyâre meant for different occasions.
Perhaps some are left to search for their very own shapes.

Seeing this, I realized that when people explore themselves or others, it is also a form of shape study.
With whatâs visible and concrete, explore the unseen and abstract.

However, good shapes only come by chance.
Shapes, in truth, cannot be good or bad in and of themselves. Itâs only when two shapes come together that the meaning thereof arises.
I hope you who decide to pick up this work will find the shapes to your liking.

metadata.name: Garden, Monoliths #44
metadata.description:
"Garden, Monoliths" is the result of an algorithm that started in April 2021. It was called "Grass.js".
Spring was blooming all around the house, taking over the stones and remnants of ancient battles that stood here. Inspiration was everywhere.
The initial goal was to use mathematical formulas for creating patterns inspired by the density of nature, that could be used by a pen plotter, so it kept focusing on outputting vector lines. This history and practice produced a graphical style based on line strokes, plus occasionally some transparent, filled shapes.
Each artwork will be either "Garden" or "Monolith", for they are variations of two existing designs from the workshop.

metadata.name: Distorted Harmony #5
metadata.description: It will happen every generation. Nothing more than an odd coincidence at best, to be chalked up to an unpredictable occurrence over the course of many years. An imprecise theory of evolution accepts that mutations take place and that these cause variations and alterations against the general classification of a species. Although the naturalist can usually stave off the taint of lacking faith or respect in the process of nature, the genetic mutation cannot.

metadata.name: Original Threads  #31
metadata.description:
Original Threads is an exploration of the winding of digital thread. Originally developed as an experiment of recreating rolls of thread in p5js, this collaboration of efforts combines se.nao.neste's core algorithmic work with Liam's drive to push as much coherent variety into a generator as possible.

At its core, this work wraps threads around a central point, subscribing to various rules as it does so. The movement of the thread is determinedÂ by the angular momentum combined with a "wander" factor.

One of the most exciting parts of the development of this algorithm was discovering and exploiting the various idiosyncracies (the peculiarities) of the drawing algorithm - the broken lines when the stroke is above a certain weight, the "burning" of the heavily layered shadows etc. - these "mistakes" we've loved and cherished and became an intrinsic part of the artistic expression of the piece.

Double-tap / hit "s" to download an image.
Add a URL parameter of "dpr" (for example ?dpr=4) to increse the resolution.
